CT of the pancreas in children.
 CT has become a frequently used imaging method for evaluating suspected pancreatic disease in children.
 Although the spectrum of CT findings in pancreatic disease is well documented in adults, there is a paucity of such information in children.
 Familiarity with CT patterns of pancreatic disease in childhood is important for diagnosis.
 In this essay, we illustrate the CT findings of pancreatic lesions in children.
